<p>I'm writing a web scraper than needs to scrape only the thumbnail of an image from the url.</p>  <p>This is my function using, the urlib library.</p>  <pre><code>def create_thumb(self):     if self.url and not self.thumbnail:         image = urllib.request.urlretrieve(self.url)          # Create the thumbnail of dimension size         size = 350, 350         t_img = Imagelib.open(image[0])         t_img.thumbnail(size)          # Get the directory name where the temp image was stored         # by urlretrieve         dir_name = os.path.dirname(image[0])          # Get the image name from the url         img_name = os.path.basename(self.url)          # Save the thumbnail in the same temp directory         # where urlretrieve got the full-sized image,         # using the same file extention in os.path.basename()         file_path = os.path.join(dir_name, "thumb" + img_name)         t_img.save(file_path)          # Save the thumbnail in the media directory, prepend thumb         self.thumbnail.save(             os.path.basename(self.url),             File(open(file_path, 'rb'))) </code></pre>  <p>for various reasons I need to change this to use the requests library, what would be the equivalent for temp saving an image?</p>